1. Remove and dispose of old deck and stairs.
2. Excavate and pour 2 caissons at a minimum of 36” deep. Install rebar cage according to engineering.
3. Cut cantilever joists at structure and install 2x8 ledger with (2) 4” ledgerlok screws @ 16” OC 
according to engineering. Install blocking as needed.
4. Build new 11’10” x 10’ deck to match existing including new staircase with 2x6 railings to match.
5. Install (2) 4x4 posts with hardware according to engineering.
6. Paint to match existing. 
7. Final Clean-up and disposal. Roll off dumpster will be onsite.
8. Engineering will be followed as it pertains to all lumber, screws, and hardware needed to build new

of a 10,572 sq.ft. floor.  This will include removal of existing,

(duct & diffusers), electrical distribution and lighting.  The demolition

new floor plans included.  This will include aligning the existing 
mechanical system distribution to the new wall configuration, 
installation of new electrical distribution & lighting, and minor 
modifications to the existing plumbing system to support new a

Project.Name: Bathroom repair - flood damage
Data:
{"status":"Issued","details":{"Applicant:":" Peter Isakovic                 Contact Number:(323) 702-1708poeticollc@gmail.com","Licensed Professional:":"ERIC YOUNG                 DENVER PROPERTY FLIP                17081 E 110TH AVE                COMMERCE CITY, CO, 80022                Home Phone:7202526888Mobile Phone:7202526888Building Contractor - Class B  LIC00245524                ","Project Description:":"Residential use as before

-Interior renovation of existing bathroom, repair from water damage, replacement of plumbing fixtures

Prior owner had sewage backup isolated to bathroom, with organic material backing up through tub drain and overflowing, flooding and damaging the wood floor, existing trim, and bathroom walls. Prior owner tried to cover-up/hide damage with taller trim and vinyl floor covering. I purchased the unit, removed the flooring, several layers of flooring underlayment, the dirty tub, the shower fixtures, the tile and the drywall in the shower/tub enclosure, the trim, and the vanity. Did a flood cut around the perimeter of the bathroom and removed the affected drywall and affected insulation. ServPro inspected and remediated and gave satisfactory report. This is a PERMIT APPLICATION FOR DRYWALL REPLACEMENT

Wall repair
-Perimeter flood cut of ~10" drywall from floor will be replaced with 5/8" water-resistant drywall, mudded, primer, textured, and entire room repainted
-Ceiling also needs minor patch/paint repair
-Drywall that was behind the vanity was damaged, so removed to start fresh and will replace with new 5/8" water-resistant/fire-resistant (two 4x8 sheets)
-Drywall will be installed with 8" screw spacing attached to the floating rails as originally installed to minimize sound transmission through isolation
-Will NOT be moving light fixture or any electric on that wall.
-Will NOT be moving any plumbing on that wall. 

Flooring
-Add acoustic flooring underlayment for sound insulation to the floor, two 3/4" OSB/plywood underlayment, Hardi-Backer, and add new floor tile. 
-need to build up 3" of finished height to make level with existing living room floor.

PLUMBING PERMIT ALREADY ISSUED
Replace with like-for-like 72" jetted tub. 
-Tub is same dimension/drain location as prior tub.
-Shower bath area will be the same dimensions
-Install new niche/shelf in shower in between studs 
-Add insulation between studs for additional sound-proofing between bath and neighboring unit
-Install new water resistant 5/8 drywall with RedGuard, Hardi-Backer, Schluter, and/or tile board, make waterproof and prep for shower wall tile. 
-Replace with new valve, diverter valve, hand shower
-add valve for hand shower valve 
-All plumbing/valve replacements and installation 
Toilet-Plumber will install new toilet
Vanity/sink
-Reusing existing bath vanity/sink and connecting to existing lines. Master plumber shall pull all required permits if/as needed
Permit already issued/posted

ELECTRICAL PERMIT ALREADY ISSUED
-Install two (2) low voltage LED lights fixtures in the ceiling over the shower area, and add light switch on wall. The existing roof systems shall be replaced in kind with new synthetic cedar shakes as appropriate to replicate the removed roofing materials. Scope includes the removal and replacement of existing gutters and downspouts with new. Portions of the existing wood soffit shall be replaced with new as indicated on the 
drawings. The wood rafter tails and fascia shall be rebuilt and repaired as needed to match existing/original size and detailing. At the brick walls, portions of the brick are to be replaced with new to match existing. Additionally, large cracks to be addressed with epoxy injections. At walls with existing wood shingles, the shingles are to be removed and replaced with new, with straight and sawtooth detailing to match existing and adjacent buildings. Portions of shingle replacement to be included as Alternate 003, see below.
Add Alternates:
Alternate 001: Replace existing exterior doors with new to match existing.
Alternate 002a: Replace existing windows on Level 1 with new to match existing.
Alternate 002b: Replace existing windows on Level 2 with new to match existing.
Alternate 003: Replace existing wood siding on the East addition with new to 
match existing. Provide stained finish.
Alternate 004: Repoint select portions of the existing brick walls as indicated on the drawings.","Owner:":"CITY & COUNTY OF DENVER *","ContactInfo":{"name":"Paul Leasure","email":"pleasure@ratiodesign.com"}},"moreDetails":{"Application Information":{"PERMIT SCOPE OF WORK":{"Minimum License Class:":"Building Contractor - Class B2"}}},"processing":{"Application Intake":[{"due":"03/22/2023","assignee":"TBD","status":"Approved","date":"05/05/2023","submitter":"Karl Mertens","text":"NOTE: Your actual review due date may vary.
